Account: Customer, Distributor and Prospect
The customers maintained in SAP (which acts as the master system) will be synchronized with the Salesforce Account object, using a new Record Type named “Customer”. This integration will be performed through the Mulesoft system, which will operate as middleware between Salesforce and the rest of the systems:

To visualize hierarchical relationships between different parent customers, the corresponding Account records will be linked using the ParentId field.

Additionally, another Record Type, Distributors, will be available within the Account object to store distributor records. This information will also come from SAP through the same interface as customers, allowing distributors to be distinguished from customers via their different Record Types.

We will also include an additional Record Type, Prospect, to allow opportunities to be associated with an unqualified lead in Salesforce (further details will be covered in the Leads section). To differentiate whether the prospect is a Customer or a Distributor, we will have these values reported in the Account Type field.

