Address: Shipping address, Billing address
A customer can have more than one billing and/or shipping address. We need to store all these customer-related addresses in a new custom object called Address. The record type indicates whether it's a billing address or a shipping address.

The remaining information required will be similar to the standard Salesforce address fields:

City – Text
Country – Text
Postal Code – Text
State/Province – Text
Street – Text
Type - Picklist: Shipping address, Billing address
Account - Master-Detail relationship to Account
Is Primary - Checkbox
External Id - Text, Unique, ExternalId
While the system supports a one-to-many (1:N) relationship—allowing an unlimited number of Shipping and Billing addresses per Account—strict data integrity rules will be enforced regarding primary designations.

For each Account, the following constraints apply:

Unique Primary Shipping: Only one Address record of type "Shipping" may be designated as Primary.
Unique Primary Billing: Only one Address record of type "Billing" may be designated as Primary.
