Data Integrity Constraints for Competitor Assets
To ensure historical data accuracy and prevent reporting discrepancies, specific restrictions will be enforced on Asset records of the Competitor Record Type.
Once a Competitor Asset has been instantiated, the following fields shall remain immutable:

Account
Business Unit
This constraint will be managed via an Apex Trigger (Before Update). The logic will compare the new and old versions of the record; if a user attempts to modify either the Account or the Business Unit, the system will block the transaction and return a custom error message.**

Should a Competitor Asset be created with incorrect data, the standard correction process is as follows:

A System Administrator must manually delete the incorrect Asset record.
A new Asset record must be generated with the correct Account and Business Unit information.
Account Landscape: Customer VoB
The Account Landscape (VoB) for Werfen and its competitors will be stored in a new custom object named Account Landscape. This approach enables us to receive Werfen-related information from SAP via integration, while allowing manual editing of the competitor-related values.

These records will be linked to the customer through a new custom field, Account__c.

Since it is necessary to define the competitor VoB values by business line, product, or test, users will be able to register this information in the Asset object. A Trigger Flow will then perform the required calculations to update the competitor VoB table values.

The calculation will be performed each time an Asset with the Competitor Record Type is created or modified, based on the business unit of the record.

