Lead: Customer Prospect and Distributor Prospect
Users must be able to create a customer prospect or distributor prospect (one that does not yet exist in the master data) in order to capture opportunities. From a new Lead record with the Customer Prospect or Distributor Prospect Record Type, an Account with the same Prospect Record Type can be generated, allowing opportunities to be associated with it.

Once an opportunity has been captured under a prospect, the system will prevent progress to the quotation stage until it is linked to a validated customer or validated distributor. SAP will be the system responsible for validating customers or distributors by updating the Account Record Type from Prospect to Customer or Distributor.

Therefore, an integration between Salesforce and SAP will be required so that Salesforce can send the Prospect records that need to be validated to the SAP system.
